The paper focuses on the development of an automated tool for detecting and analyzing ransomware behavior using machine learning techniques. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of visualization techniques to aid in malware forensic efforts, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of large volumes of data, which could be relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
